    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="687"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.77/85.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commander of the U. S. S.
                            “Petrel”</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of the
                        Navy</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Petrel</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Puerto Cortés</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I am informed by the American Consul that the authorities will seize the railroad
                    today. The superintendent of road refuses to give up unless he receives orders
                    from New York. Consul requested me to protect the lives and property of American
                    citizens. If necessary I will by force prevent seizure until I hear from the
                    Department. Instructions from the Department are requested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dismukes</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
